    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Understood. You want something punchier, less sprawling than Option 1, but still respectful enough not to cause a major diplomatic incident. I can certainly trim that down for you.\n\nHere is a shorter, more direct version. It gets straight to the point while still giving them the necessary positive reinforcement. It’s efficient, which is good, because sometimes the best way to handle a tough decision is to be brief, not overly verbose.\n\n**Option 2: Direct and Respectful**\n\nSubject: Update on the Senior Developer Role at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you again for making it to the final stage for the Senior Developer role. We sincerely appreciated the time you took to interview with our team; your skills in system design and cultural fit were truly impressive. It was a very competitive final round, which made this decision particularly challenging.\n\nWhile your candidacy was extremely strong, we have decided to proceed with another candidate whose background aligned most closely with our immediate requirements. We wish you the very best in your job search and future endeavors.\n\nWe hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n\n***\n\n*See how that is?* It’",
      "source": "target",
